    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe position of the cursor (reported by `nvim_win_get_cursor()`) is changed by setting a mark.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n## Steps\r\n\r\n1. Create _tmp.lua_ with the following:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal c1 = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0) \r\nvim.cmd[[ normal! ma ]]                   \r\nlocal c2 = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0) \r\nprint(c1[2], c2[2])       \r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Run:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nnvim --clean tmp.lua\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Run `:source` . Column reported by `nvim_win_get_cursor()` differs after the `normal! ma` command.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Additional notes\r\n\r\nWhile the cursor does not move, its reported column is off by 1.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nColumn output should report unchanged, just as setting a mark in normal mode would.\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n:h mark\r\n```\r\n\r\n```help\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t*m* *mark* *Mark*\r\nm{a-zA-Z}\t\tSet mark {a-zA-Z} at cursor position (does not move\r\n\t\t\tthe cursor, this is not a motion command).\r\n```\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.9.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.13.1 (fe2a3c56)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
